\begin_inset Formula $\int_{D=\infty}(p/p^{\star})p^{\star}d\mu>0$
\end_inset

 too.
 It follows that 
\begin_inset Formula $P(D=\infty)>0$
\end_inset

, and, since 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

 is aribtrary, 
\begin_inset Formula $D$
\end_inset

 has infinite diameter with positive probability.
\end_layout

